<br>
Here we see the consequence of incautious overhype.  The screenshots sure DID make it seem as though the criticals were happening 25 percent!  And the only problem with this is that we have the hard numbers from Verant themselves: 7 percent.  Posting ideallic screenshots is, as we can witness from above, effectively misinformation.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarkaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkaan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/1/02 6:25:53 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://arkaan.dhs.org:88/eq/arksig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Casting Fury</span><hr size=1> From what I understand about SCF:<br>
<br>
SCF lvl 1 is a 2% chance of landing a 133% dmg crit.<br>
SCF lvl 2 is a 4% chance of landing a 166% dmg crit.<br>
SCF lvl 3 is a 7% chance of landing a 200% dmg crit.<br>
<br>
So you will NOT land crits 25% of the time, you will land them 7% of the time.  However, depending on the current seed that the roll is calculated on (if this is how its done), you may get a few crits in a row.  But the overall average is probably still going to hover at a little below 10% <p><center>-----------------------------------------<br>
